subject: Re: Urgent: Users unable to access resources with correct permissions
message_body: John, we've identified the issue. There was a temporary system error affecting IAM role synchronization. This has now been resolved.  Could you please ask your users to log out and log back in? This should refresh their permissions.  We apologize for the inconvenience this caused. Let us know if you encounter any further problems.

subject: Re: URGENT: IAM Role Issues Causing API Gateway Errors
message_body: Thank you for contacting Aetheros support. We understand you are experiencing urgent issues with your IAM roles and API Gateway. Can you please provide us with the specific IAM roles and API endpoints affected? Also, confirm the region of your cloud deployment managed by Aetheros. This information will help us investigate further.

subject: Re: URGENT: Cloud resources unavailable after IAM role change
message_body: This issue has been resolved. Please confirm if you are able to access your cloud resources now. We will be conducting a thorough investigation into the root cause of this issue to prevent similar incidents in the future.

message_body:

I've tried reviewing the documentation and searching your forums, but haven't found a solution yet. Could you please help me understand what I might be doing wrong?

Here's a snippet of the code I'm using:

```mercury
let response = await http.get("https://example.com/api/data");
log(response);
```

Any help would be greatly appreciated.

Thanks,
John Doe
